Backing Up DD-WRT Settings Using HTTrack
Disclaimer: This does not backup 100% of the settings in DD-WRT, but it is a great way to capture the settings prior to upgrading so values can be copied/pasted back into place

Download HTTrack Download
Extract the download hhtrack-noinst zip archive
Create a directory to store your DD-WRT backup
Launch WinHTTrack.exe
Click Next
Set Project name: DD-WRT
Set Base path to the directory created in step 3
Click Next
Click Add URL...
Set URL: to your DD-WRT IP Address
Login: your DD-WRT user name
Password: your DD-WRT password

Click OK
Click Next
Wait for the process to complete
Browse the site created by HTTrack
